& [FocusResolutionRefinement070] is the realized focus-refinement frame
  + [moment] is focusing on focusing revealed that the system already has strong rails but needs sharper quality, membrane, gradient, receipt, and shadow-horizon surfaces
  + [focus] is focus resolution refinement
  + [inside] is focus_quality, focus_membrane, periphery_gradient, active_question_stack, attention_runtime_registry, attention_stack_frame, contrast_pair, integration_receipt, understanding_ladder, shadow_scan, horizon_scan, caution_debt, and wisdom_yield
  + [boundary] is these are refinement supports for existing focus, Wisdom, Caution, traversal, and balance systems; they are not proof of hidden cognition or complete understanding
  + [outside] is AGI proof, hidden activations, exhaustive completeness, arbitrary association, and photonic fork continuation
  + [wisdom] is the additions fit because they make existing focus operations more inspectable, returnable, and integrable
  + [caution] is the additions remain bounded as contracts/proposals until used and tested in future focus passes
  + [balance] is stable because the refinement reduces flood and collapse risk by adding membrane and gradient controls
  + [next_step] is apply FocusResolutionRefinement to the current awareness-node focal stream by creating an example attention_stack_frame or integration receipt on a later pass

  = must: keep shadow and horizon distinct from evidence
  = must: use integration_receipt before calling a focus result durable understanding
  = should: treat focus_quality as visible orientation, not proof of truth

/ [focus_on_focusing], [periphery_zoom], [wisdom_caution] -(Reveals)> [FocusResolutionRefinement], [resolution_outside]
* [focus_membrane], [periphery_gradient], [attention_runtime_registry], [integration_receipt] -(Improves)> [focus_quality], [integrated_understanding], [outside]
